{{Infobox University| name= Uzbekistan State Institute of Arts and Culture named after [[Mannon Uygʻur]]| native_name=Ўзбекистон Давлат санъат ва маданият институти| image=| latin_name=| motto=| established=1945 | type=| staff= | rector= Bakhtier Sayfullaev | faculty=| city=[[Tashkent]]| country=[[Uzbekistan]]| campus= | affiliations= | website={{URL|http://www.dsmi.uz/}} | |students= }} '''Uzbekistan State Institute of Arts and Culture''' is a higher education institution in [[Uzbekistan]]. The institute was founded in 1945 as theatre and artistic art Institute named after [[Alexander Ostrovsky]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uzdoc.eu/organization/uzbekistan-state-institute-arts-and |title= Uzbekistan State Institute of Arts and Culture |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date= 2017-03-26 |quote=}}</ref> Uzbekistan State institute of Arts and Culture was formed according to the decree № PP-1771 from June 4, 2012 year of the [[President of Uzbekistan]] on the basis of Uzbekistan Institute of Arts and Tashkent State Institute of Culture after A.Kadiri.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uzdoc.eu/sites/default/files/uzsiac_presentation.pdf |title=Uzbekistan State Institute of Arts and Culture |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher= UZDOC (doctoral studies in Uzbekistan) |access-date= 2017-03-26 |quote=}}</ref> Nowadays it is [[Central Asia]]’s major training school in the fields of cinema, television, theatre and design.<ref>{{cite book |date= |year= 2005 |orig-year= |chapter= |script-chapter= |trans-chapter= |chapter-url= |chapter-format= |editor1-last= Brisbane |editor1-first= Katherine |editor1-link= Katherine Brisbane |editor2-last= Chaturvedi |editor2-first= Ravi |editor2-link= Ravi Chaturvedi |editor3-last= Majumdar |editor3-first= Ramendu |editor3-link= Ramendu Majumdar |editor4-last= Pong |editor4-first= Chua Soo |editor4-link= Chua Soo Pong |editor5-last= Tanokura |editor5-first= Minoru |editor5-link= Minoru Tanokura |display-editors= |title= The [[World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre]] |script-title= |trans-title= |url= |dead-url= |format= |type= |series= |language= |volume= Volume 5: Asia/Pacific |issue= |others= |edition= |location= |publisher= [[Routledge]] |publication-date= |page= |pages= 573 |at= |nopp= |arxiv= |asin= |bibcode= |doi= |doi-broken-date= |isbn= |issn= |jfm= |jstor= |lccn= |mr= |oclc= |ol= |osti= |pmc= |pmid= |rfc= |ssrn= |zbl= |id= |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date= |via= |registration= |subscription= |lay-summary= |lay-source= |lay-date= |quote= |name-list-format= |mode= |postscript= |ref= }}</ref> The institute consists of 3 faculties: * Dramatic art * Art of Film, Television and Radio * Folk art
